            <title>[SUREFIRE-1561] Logs in Parallel Tests are mixed up when forkMode=never or forkCount=0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SUREFIRE-1561</link>
                <project id="12317927" key="SUREFIRE">Maven Surefire (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Out integration test &lt;tt&gt;Surefire1177TestngParallelSuitesIT&lt;/tt&gt; fails.&lt;br/&gt;
On Ubuntu/Linux it looks like the messages are mix up when the tests run in parallel.&lt;br/&gt;
The root cause is a method which is not synchronized.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;TestSetRunListener#writeTestOutput( byte[] buf, int off, int len, boolean stdout )&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
